events.name: Oklahoma City Thunder at Washington Wizards

headlines.description: — The Washington Wizards pulled out another close game, this time with their biggest star sidelined.

— Devin Booker scored 16 points, including the go-ahead basket with 1:02 remaining, and Chris Paul had 15 points and 12 assists as the Phoenix Suns beat Toronto 99-95 on Tuesday night to snap the Raptors’ longest winning streak of the season at six...
headlines.shortLinkText: Booker scores 16 as Suns cool off streaking Raptors, 99-95

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Memphis Grizzlies

headlines.description: — Ja Morant scored 29 points, including five in the final minute, and the Memphis Grizzlies beat the Golden State Warriors 116-108 Tuesday night for their 10th straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morant scores 29, Grizzlies beat Warriors for 10th straight

events.name: Minnesota Timberwolves at New Orleans Pelicans

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram threw both arms above his head, extending three fingers on each hand and smiling triumphantly as his Pelicans teammates and fans celebrated wildly.
headlines.shortLinkText: Ingram's 3 late 3s lift Pelicans past Timberwolves 128-125

headlines.description: — Nikola Vučević scored 22 points, DeMar DeRozan had 20 points and 12 rebounds, and the Chicago Bulls routed the Detroit Pistons 133-87 on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Vučević, DeRozan lift Bulls over Pistons 133-87

headlines.description: — Amir Coffey had 18 points, Reggie Jackson scored 11 of his 13 in the fourth quarter and the Los Angeles Clippers rallied from a 25-point deficit in the second half for a stunning 87-85 victory over the Denver Nuggets on Tuesday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Clippers rally from 25 down in 2nd half, stun Nuggets 87-85
